Description:<br>
Luxury Perfume is looking for a highly capable and goal oriented store manager at its retail locations at<br>
<br>
<br>
1815 Hawthorne Blvd. #201 Redondo Beach, CA 90278<br>
<br>
Position Overview:<br>
<br>
The Store manager will be responsible for the following core responsibilities which includes:<br>
<br>
- Recruiting and developing staff to be dedicated to meeting and exceeding goals<br>
<br>
- Insure that customer service are met to the highest standards<br>
<br>
- Ensure that merchandise is well accounted for and are handled appropriately<br>
<br>
- Make an efficient communication with other departments to ensure smooth operations<br>
<br>
- Enforce all company policies and procedure consistently<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Other Key Areas of Responsibilities:<br>
<br>
- Strong communication, presentation and interpersonal skills.<br>
<br>
- High energy and charisma that seeks to socialize and to make customers and staff feel comfortable.<br>
<br>
- Regular, consistent and punctual attendance. Must be able to work nights and weekends, variable schedule(s) from the hours of 9am-10pm as necessary.<br>
<br>
- A strong ability to work independently and effectively.<br>
<br>
- Ability to use company systems in regards to processing sales for the customer (i.e. POS retail sales system)<br>
<br>
- Compensation will be salary based with bonuses based on sales goals. Amount will be discussed at time of job offer.<br>
<br>
- Fluent English mandatory<br>
<br>
- Bilingual Spanish is a PLUS<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Qualifications:<br>
<br>
- Experience in retail processes with proven success in sales quota achievement a major plus.<br>
<br>
- Bachelors or Associates Degree and a minimum of 2-3 year(s) retail experience (References required)<br>
<br>
- Must be able to stand for long periods of time.<br>
<br>
- Minimal lifting (2-5 pounds) required.    </section>

